Consider the target `sorry` in `IsBinomialRandom.compl`. We need to prove that if $G \sim G(V, p)$, then $G^c \sim G(V, \sigma p)$.
The definition `binomialRandom` is `Ber(diagSetᶜ, p).comap edgeSet`.
We know that `Ber(S, \sigma p)` is the image of `Ber(S, p)` under the map $s \mapsto s^c \cap S$.
Let $S = \text{diagSet}^c$. The map is $\Phi(s) = s^c \cap S$.
We also know that `edgeSet (G^c) = (edgeSet G)^c \cap S = \Phi(\text{edgeSet } G)`.
So `edgeSet \circ compl = \Phi \circ edgeSet`.
The equality of measures `map compl (comap edgeSet Ber) = comap edgeSet (map \Phi Ber)` follows from this commutation and the fact that `Ber` is supported on the range of `edgeSet` (subsets of $S$).

